\begin_layout Standard
While debt service has been the fastest growing liability for counties in
 Colorado (+633%), it still remains a small portion of the overall budget
 (4.7% in 2009).
 The dominant liability resides with operating expenditures.
 Given the preponderence of direct spending activity at the local level,
 this is unsurprising.
 Operating expenditures increased 116% over the period, but fell as a percentage
 of total expenditures (79% to 76%).
 Within operating expenditures, the fastest growing line item was judicial
 expenditure (+263%), although it constituted only 3.6% of operating expenditures
 in 2009.
 The real story is in public safety, which grew 231% over the period.
 This spending increased its compositional importance notably, growing from
