 Blue squares indicate weight values of 1, so those jurisdictions are 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

all in
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, so to speak.
 Binary classification of neighbors is in no way a requirement.
 The strength of the weight may vary with proximity, and there are a number
 of decay functions in common use.
 This study employs three kinds: binary, inverse distance, and Gaussian.
 Generic examples of these are depicted in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
