\end_layout

\end_inset

) is the most direct measure of housing demand.
 There are reasons for both the population growth and permit rate indicators
 to separate from stock utilization.
 For example, population growth may be accompanied by increases in household
 size and permit rates may increase due to developer forecasting assumptions.
 Neither separation is possible with the vacancy rate.
\end_layout

