\begin_layout Standard
When controlling for other factors, COTEL intensity (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$intensity
\backslash
_stock$
\end_layout

\end_inset

) has very limited impact on the clustering of revenue yield (
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$pcrev$
\end_layout

\end_inset

).
 Said differently, if a county is highly constrained, the constraint is
 not a significant driver of the clustering that already exists.
\end_layout

